Nods for Best Picture - The Kids Are All Right
2011-01-30 05:51:08 GMT
Director Lisa Cholodenko's The Kids Are All Right picked up a nom for Best Picture. The critically acclaimed indie film, part comedy and part drama, follows a lesbian couple in Los Angeles raising their two children. When the children's biological father enters back into the picture, the entire family's lives are thrown into disarray.The Kids Are All Right is a 2010 American drama film directed by Lisa Cholodenko and written by Cholodenko and Stuart Blumberg.One of Sundance 2010's breakout hits, it opened in limited release on July 9, 2010, expanding to more theaters on July 30, 2010. It was released on DVD and Blu-ray on November 16, 2010. The film was awarded the Golden Globe Award for Best Motion Picture - Musical or Comedy, and Annette Bening was awarded the Golden Globe Award for Best Actress â€“ Motion Picture Musical or Comedy. The film also got Nominated for 4 Academy Awards, including a Nomination for Best Picture, at the 83rd Academy Awards.
